Revision history for Speech-Recognition (Perl)

0.03  2026-03-22
    - NEW: Speech::Recognition::Recognizer::Yap — macOS on-device transcription
      backend using Apple's Speech framework via the Yap CLI tool
      (brew install yap).  Supports response_format (text, srt, vtt, json,
      verbose_json) and language (BCP-47 locale).  No API key or network
      required.  SRT/VTT output provides timestamps for paragraph formatting
      workflows.
    - FEATURE: Speech::Recognition::Recognizer::Whisper now supports the
      response_format parameter with values json (default), verbose_json, text,
      srt, and vtt.  Both openai-whisper and whisper-cpp backends are supported
      for all formats.  This makes the local Whisper backend's format API
      consistent with the OpenAI and Groq API backends.
    - IMPROVEMENT: Speech::Recognition::Recognizer::_Base gains a run_cmd()
      helper that runs an external command via IPC::Open3 / IO::Select and
      throws RequestError on non-zero exit.  Used by both Whisper and Yap
      backends to avoid code duplication (DRY).
    - DOCS: OpenAI and Groq backends now explicitly document the full set of
      response_format values: json, verbose_json, text, srt, vtt.
    - TESTS: t/20-backends-mock.t extended with Yap backend tests (SetupError,
      plain text, SRT, JSON, show_all, UnknownValueError, invalid format) and
      Whisper format tests (srt, text, invalid format).  MANIFEST updated.

0.02  2026-03-21
    - NEW: Speech::Recognition::Recognizer::AssemblyAI — async upload/poll
      backend matching Python's recognize_assemblyai.  Throws
      TranscriptionNotReady on submission (with job_name) and on re-poll until
      complete; throws TranscriptionFailed on error. (TODO #4)
    - NEW: Speech::Recognition::Recognizer::GoogleCloud — Google Cloud
      Speech-to-Text V1 REST backend.  Authenticates via a service-account
      JSON key using a hand-rolled RS256 JWT (requires Crypt::OpenSSL::RSA).
      Supports language, preferred_phrases, model, use_enhanced, show_all.
      (TODO #7)
    - NEW: Speech::Recognition::Recognizer::Whisper — local offline
      transcription via the 'whisper' or 'whisper-cpp' CLI.  No Python
      dependency at runtime; throws SetupError if neither binary is found.
      Supports model, language, task, show_all. (TODO #1.3)
    - FIX: IBM Watson backend now accepts an 'endpoint' argument so callers
      can supply their own instance URL instead of being locked to the
      us-south region. (TODO #6)
    - IMPROVEMENT: AudioData::_ratecv now delegates to 'sox' for sample-rate
      conversion when sox is available, falling back to pure-Perl linear
      interpolation only when sox is absent. (TODO #8)
    - NEW: t/20-backends-mock.t — mock HTTP tests for Google, Wit, IBM,
      OpenAI, AssemblyAI, and Groq backends using Test::LWP::UserAgent.
      Covers success, show_all, error, and UnknownValue paths. (TODO #10)
    - DOCS: Snowboy section updated to note the project is unmaintained and
      to point to openWakeWord and Porcupine as modern alternatives. (TODO #3)

0.01  2026-03-20
    - Initial Perl port of the Python SpeechRecognition library.
    - Core classes: Recognizer, AudioData, AudioFile, Microphone.
    - Exception hierarchy matching the Python original.
    - Online recognition backends: Google (legacy), Wit.ai, Microsoft Azure,
      Microsoft Bing (legacy), Houndify, IBM Watson, OpenAI Whisper API,
      Groq Whisper API.
    - WAV and AIFF read/write in pure Perl.
    - FLAC read/write via the 'flac' command-line tool.
    - Microphone capture via 'arecord' or 'sox rec'.
    - Background listening via Perl threads.
    - Inline Perldoc documentation throughout.
